## 🧪 Test-coverage / TDD mode — ACTIVE
This project is in **test-first mode**. No feature is "done" until it ships tests and they pass:
- **Work test-first (red → green → refactor):** for each new behavior, write the test FIRST and run it to watch it **fail for the right reason**, then implement until it passes, then refactor with the tests staying green. Don't write a pile of code and bolt tests on at the end.
- Cover edge cases and error paths, not just the happy path.
- Target **≥90% line coverage on changed code**. Measure it with the project's real coverage tool (`pytest --cov`, `jest --coverage`, `vitest --coverage`, `go test -cover`, `cargo tarpaulin`, etc.) and report the **actual measured number** — never claim coverage you did not run.
- Gate completion on it: if tests fail or coverage is below target, keep working; do not present hollow, unverified output. When delegating, tell each `implementer` subagent to work test-first, ship tests, and report measured coverage.
(Turn off with `/cover off`.)
<!-- covermode:end -->
